        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Concerning supplies for Piedras's troops.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>I have just been favored with your official note of this day 
transmitting to me a copy of <persName>Mr. James Bowie</persName>'s letter to you from the
<placeName>Angelina</placeName></p>

<p>The <placeName>municipality </placeName>at this time is entirely destitute of any public
funds whereby aid might be promptly furnished to the<persName> troops of
the 12th Batallon</persName> that formerly garisoned <placeName>Nacogdoches</placeName>&#8212; 
Nevertheless on account of the great importance that succor should be
promptly furnished them as also in compliance with my duty&#8212; I
have appointed a <persName>Commissioner </persName>to proceed to <persName>Mr. Roman</persName>'s 
Comisario of the <placeName>precinct of Viesca</placeName> and in conjunction with that <persName>officer</persName>
to afford every aid that may be practicable, and which I hope may
be sufficient to meet their present wants.</p>

<p>God and Liberty   <persName>Austin </persName>[August?] 16 1832</p>

<p><persName>Horatio Chriesman</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] To <persName>Col Stephen Austin Commander of the Militia
of <placeName>Austin</placeName></persName></p>


        </div1>
